ce:section.ce:para:
The importance of the anionic exchange with OH− was obvious during controlling the morphology, active surface area and edge/basal planes of nanocarbons such as GQDs. For this purpose, the BET/BJH analyses were evaluated throughout interaction with OH− at various potential steps. Compared to the active surface area (as
                        ), pore volume (Vp
                        ), and pore radius (rp
                        ) of bare GQDs (Table 1
                        ), significant promotion was observed in the samples by the intercalation with OH− at potential of −0.2V. In addition major reduction was observed in the active surface area through the treatment with NO3
                        − (Table 1).
